comments.body:
Hi [~yangjiandan], I just committed a patch to enable generic AM simulators for synthetic load generation, and after giving this patch a quick read through, I think you'll run into some merging issues. Let me know if you have any questions about the code I committed, I'll be happy to help.

On a side note, I was actually looking to enable Opportunistic containers in SLS, so I'm very much looking forward to this patch!

Quick question: What's the purpose of adding the "water level" to the NMSimulator?

 
{code:java}
    if (waterLevel > 0 && waterLevel <=1) {
      int pMemUsed = (int) (node.getTotalCapability().getMemorySize() * waterLevel);
      float cpuUsed = node.getTotalCapability().getVirtualCores() * waterLevel;
      ResourceUtilization resourceUtilization = ResourceUtilization.newInstance(pMemUsed, pMemUsed, cpuUsed);
      ns.setContainersUtilization(resourceUtilization);
      ns.setNodeUtilization(resourceUtilization);
    }
{code}

+1 from me. Small nit with the current patch, could we set a default execution type for the synth format? Something like: 

 
{code:java}
@JsonProperty("execution_type")
String executionType = ExecutionType.GUARANTEED.name();
{code}
should do the trick. Thanks for working on this [~yangjiandan] and [~cheersyang]!

